## Issue

### Invalid YAML frontmatter — `description` field contains unquoted `: ` sequences

**Files:** 11 across decisions + research/lessons.

The dense paragraph `description` fields contain `: ` (colon + space) sequences which YAML interprets as nested-mapping syntax. Standard YAML parsers (including the one Claude Code uses to read frontmatter for memory context) reject these with `mapping values are not allowed here`.

Verified empirically with Python `yaml.safe_load`:
- `single_entry_pipeline.md` line 2 col 325 — fails on "responsibilities: ENTRY"
- `memory_scope_split.md` line 2 col 126 — fails on "invocations: developer"
- `ajv_migration_attempt.md` line 2 col 406 — fails on "RECOMMEND-REVERT: ajv"

This means the auto-loaded memory in Claude Code is silently failing to parse the new frontmatter, dropping the description field from the agent's context. That's worse than the pre-Tier-1 baseline.

**Fix:** Convert all `description` values to YAML folded scalar (`>-`) form:

```yaml
description: >-
  Dense paragraph text with colons: safe under YAML. Line breaks
  become spaces within the paragraph; trailing newline trimmed.
```

This is the standard YAML pattern for paragraph-length values and reads naturally in plain text. Apply consistently to ALL files in `docs/decisions/` and `docs/research/`, not just the 11 codex flagged — the convention should be uniform across the memory tree.

Verify with a parse check across the entire set after the fix.

